		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:06,200",
				"to": "00:06:11,360"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 366200,
				"to": 371360
			},
			"text": " For example, you can always create wrapper contracts in the worst case."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:11,360",
				"to": "00:06:18,160"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 371360,
				"to": 378160
			},
			"text": " And the other point that is necessary, in my opinion, is to define a pseudo-instrumental"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:18,160",
				"to": "00:06:19,160"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 378160,
				"to": 379160
			},
			"text": " standard."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:19,160",
				"to": "00:06:25,360"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 379160,
				"to": 385360
			},
			"text": " Mainly pseudo-instrumental means that you can ask to a smart contract about the implementation"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:25,360",
				"to": "00:06:28,400"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 385360,
				"to": 388400
			},
			"text": " of a specific interface."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:28,400",
				"to": "00:06:33,280"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 388400,
				"to": 393280
			},
			"text": " To standardize this, we currently have two very different proposals."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:33,280",
				"to": "00:06:37,920"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 393280,
				"to": 397920
			},
			"text": " EAP 165 and EAP 672."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:37,920",
				"to": "00:06:42,480"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 397920,
				"to": 402480
			},
			"text": " EAP 165 is very straightforward."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:42,480",
				"to": "00:06:50,880"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 402480,
				"to": 410880
			},
			"text": " You just define a support interface function that is the smart contract may implement."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:50,880",
				"to": "00:06:55,480"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 410880,
				"to": 415480
			},
			"text": " Then anyone can use this function to query if this contract implements a specific interface"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:55,480",
				"to": "00:06:58,440"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 415480,
				"to": 418440
			},
			"text": " or not."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:06:58,440",
				"to": "00:07:05,760"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 418440,
				"to": 425760
			},
			"text": " The other proposal, EAP 672, in my opinion, makes more sense and it's much more scalable."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:05,760",
				"to": "00:07:14,480"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 425760,
				"to": 434480
			},
			"text": " The idea of EAP 672 is to use reverse ENS to keep a database of interfaces implemented"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:14,480",
				"to": "00:07:17,240"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 434480,
				"to": 437240
			},
			"text": " on each existing contract."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:17,240",
				"to": "00:07:21,360"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 437240,
				"to": 441360
			},
			"text": " Let me give you an example of how this would work."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:21,360",
				"to": "00:07:26,720"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 441360,
				"to": 446720
			},
			"text": " Imagine that a contract implements a token fallback interface and the constructor of the"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:26,720",
				"to": "00:07:34,000"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 446720,
				"to": 454000
			},
			"text": " token would add this entry in the reverse ENS."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:34,000",
				"to": "00:07:40,240"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 454000,
				"to": 460240
			},
			"text": " For people that don't know how reverse ENS works, it mainly defines a domain for each"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:40,240",
				"to": "00:07:41,240"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 460240,
				"to": 461240
			},
			"text": " address."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:41,240",
				"to": "00:07:45,520"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 461240,
				"to": 465520
			},
			"text": " Normally this address is assigned to a human readable name, so you can set a name for your"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:45,520",
				"to": "00:07:46,720"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 465520,
				"to": 466720
			},
			"text": " address."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:46,720",
				"to": "00:07:52,640"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 466720,
				"to": 472640
			},
			"text": " But you have full control of this special domain assigned to your address."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:52,640",
				"to": "00:07:55,280"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 472640,
				"to": 475280
			},
			"text": " So you can create subdomains."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:07:55,280",
				"to": "00:08:01,440"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 475280,
				"to": 481440
			},
			"text": " In our case, we define a subdomain with the interface name that the contract implements"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:01,440",
				"to": "00:08:06,240"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 481440,
				"to": 486240
			},
			"text": " and make it point to the address responsible for implementing the interface."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:06,240",
				"to": "00:08:14,480"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 486240,
				"to": 494480
			},
			"text": " In most cases, this will point to itself if the contract implements the interface."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:14,480",
				"to": "00:08:20,880"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 494480,
				"to": 500880
			},
			"text": " But that's not strictly necessary and this is where the standard gets interesting."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:20,880",
				"to": "00:08:25,200"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 500880,
				"to": 505200
			},
			"text": " This entry can point to a different proxy contract."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:25,200",
				"to": "00:08:27,280"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 505200,
				"to": 507280
			},
			"text": " Think about it."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:27,280",
				"to": "00:08:34,040"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 507280,
				"to": 514040
			},
			"text": " This allows for future functionalities and future interface to be easily supported when"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:34,040",
				"to": "00:08:36,560"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 514040,
				"to": 516560
			},
			"text": " they come."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:36,560",
				"to": "00:08:42,240"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 516560,
				"to": 522240
			},
			"text": " Coming back to the ERC 2 to 3 standard, one of the biggest shortcomings is that it cannot"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:42,240",
				"to": "00:08:48,520"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 522240,
				"to": 528520
			},
			"text": " transfer tokens to the current multi-sec implementation because they are contracts that don't implement"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:48,520",
				"to": "00:08:51,680"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 528520,
				"to": 531680
			},
			"text": " the token fallback function."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:51,680",
				"to": "00:08:56,760"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 531680,
				"to": 536760
			},
			"text": " To work around this, a new version of the multi-sec should be deployed."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:08:56,760",
				"to": "00:09:06,280"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 536760,
				"to": 546280
			},
			"text": " But this can't be solved easily with EIP 6.7.2 by creating a reverse DNS entry for the"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:06,280",
				"to": "00:09:13,200"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 546280,
				"to": 553200
			},
			"text": " eye token fallback interface that points to a proxy contract that just accepts the transfer."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:13,200",
				"to": "00:09:14,640"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 553200,
				"to": 554640
			},
			"text": " And this is very exciting."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:14,640",
				"to": "00:09:20,880"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 554640,
				"to": 560880
			},
			"text": " This also gives the possibility of executing some code not only when tokens are sent to"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:20,880",
				"to": "00:09:27,000"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 560880,
				"to": 567000
			},
			"text": " a contract, but also when tokens are sent to a regular account."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:27,000",
				"to": "00:09:34,320"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 567000,
				"to": 574320
			},
			"text": " If you assign a proxy to a regular account, you can, for example, prevent receiving a"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:34,320",
				"to": "00:09:40,120"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 574320,
				"to": 580120
			},
			"text": " payment you don't want or trigger any code you desire when a regular account receives"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:40,120",
				"to": "00:09:47,360"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 580120,
				"to": 587360
			},
			"text": " tokens."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:47,360",
				"to": "00:09:53,080"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 587360,
				"to": 593080
			},
			"text": " At this point, if you put together all the minimifunctionality and the ERC 2 to 3 token"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:09:53,080",
				"to": "00:10:00,960"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 593080,
				"to": 600960
			},
			"text": " with the EIP 6.7.2, we get a super flexible contract."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:00,960",
				"to": "00:10:05,680"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 600960,
				"to": 605680
			},
			"text": " This is the new token contract given it is working on right now."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:05,680",
				"to": "00:10:08,200"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 605680,
				"to": 608200
			},
			"text": " We call it internally yoga token."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:08,200",
				"to": "00:10:11,560"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 608200,
				"to": 611560
			},
			"text": " You can imagine in choir."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:11,560",
				"to": "00:10:17,520"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 611560,
				"to": 617520
			},
			"text": " In my opinion, this yoga token could be a perfect candidate to be considered for a standard"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:17,520",
				"to": "00:10:23,200"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 617520,
				"to": 623200
			},
			"text": " Ethereum token, especially if Ethereum-based government systems, like carbon boating or"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:23,200",
				"to": "00:10:26,280"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 623200,
				"to": 626280
			},
			"text": " protocol boating, are to be developed."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:26,280",
				"to": "00:10:31,860"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 626280,
				"to": 631860
			},
			"text": " Of course, the gas problem may still be an issue, but this can be minimized by enforcing"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:31,860",
				"to": "00:10:38,760"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 631860,
				"to": 638760
			},
			"text": " only EIPOC snapshots instead of block snapshots."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:38,760",
				"to": "00:10:42,160"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 638760,
				"to": 642160
			},
			"text": " How do you finish this talk?"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:42,160",
				"to": "00:10:44,560"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 642160,
				"to": 644560
			},
			"text": " I would like to introduce liquid pledging."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:44,560",
				"to": "00:10:49,680"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 644560,
				"to": 649680
			},
			"text": " This is one of the main open source smart contracts that have been developed at GIBF."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:49,680",
				"to": "00:10:55,040"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 649680,
				"to": 655040
			},
			"text": " While not exactly a token contract, it extends some powerful functionality that can be applied"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:55,040",
				"to": "00:10:56,880"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 655040,
				"to": 656880
			},
			"text": " to any token."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:56,880",
				"to": "00:10:59,800"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 656880,
				"to": 659800
			},
			"text": " What's liquid pledging about?"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:10:59,800",
				"to": "00:11:04,840"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 659800,
				"to": 664840
			},
			"text": " Liquid pledging is where liquid democracy meets fund management."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:04,840",
				"to": "00:11:12,320"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 664840,
				"to": 672320
			},
			"text": " Essentially, you can manage your tokens or let someone else manage them with oversight."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:12,320",
				"to": "00:11:14,840"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 672320,
				"to": 674840
			},
			"text": " With a normal wallet, you manage your tokens."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:14,840",
				"to": "00:11:20,960"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 674840,
				"to": 680960
			},
			"text": " You have a balance, you have transfer functions, inputs, outputs, and that's effectively all."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:20,960",
				"to": "00:11:27,440"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 680960,
				"to": 687440
			},
			"text": " With liquid pledging, not only you can manage your own tokens, but you can also manage someone"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:27,440",
				"to": "00:11:29,800"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 687440,
				"to": 689800
			},
			"text": " else's tokens."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:29,800",
				"to": "00:11:34,200"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 689800,
				"to": 694200
			},
			"text": " You do this by creating a hierarchical chain of delegation."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:34,200",
				"to": "00:11:37,520"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 694200,
				"to": 697520
			},
			"text": " You can give the authority of the tokens to a delegate."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:37,520",
				"to": "00:11:43,120"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 697520,
				"to": 703120
			},
			"text": " The delegate can do the same with a sub-delegate and so on."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:43,120",
				"to": "00:11:48,800"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 703120,
				"to": 708800
			},
			"text": " The most important feature is that after good delegate the tokens, you are still empowered"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:48,800",
				"to": "00:11:53,000"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 708800,
				"to": 713000
			},
			"text": " to make decisions regarding the use of these tokens."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:53,000",
				"to": "00:11:57,480"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 713000,
				"to": 717480
			},
			"text": " As the owner, you have the complete oversight."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:11:57,480",
				"to": "00:12:04,040"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 717480,
				"to": 724040
			},
			"text": " To make it clear, let me give you an example."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:04,040",
				"to": "00:12:10,640"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 724040,
				"to": 730640
			},
			"text": " One is a community member that's very concerned for security in the blockchain and wants to"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:10,640",
				"to": "00:12:17,000"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 730640,
				"to": 737000
			},
			"text": " donate 100 Ether to projects that improve security."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:17,000",
				"to": "00:12:23,480"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 737000,
				"to": 743480
			},
			"text": " He wants to do good, but he's a very busy person and don't have the time to analyze"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:23,480",
				"to": "00:12:26,280"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 743480,
				"to": 746280
			},
			"text": " all the projects in the space."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:26,280",
				"to": "00:12:31,760"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 746280,
				"to": 751760
			},
			"text": " On the other hand, we have Wookie, who is a very active member of the community and also"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:31,760",
				"to": "00:12:34,960"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 751760,
				"to": 754960
			},
			"text": " very much concerned with security."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:34,960",
				"to": "00:12:41,360"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 754960,
				"to": 761360
			},
			"text": " He has complete overview of all the projects in the space and now which key projects should"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:41,360",
				"to": "00:12:43,480"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 761360,
				"to": 763480
			},
			"text": " be supported."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:43,480",
				"to": "00:12:51,000"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 763480,
				"to": 771000
			},
			"text": " With liquid pledging, GAB can delegate the authority over his 100 Ether to Bokey so he"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:51,000",
				"to": "00:12:53,600"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 771000,
				"to": 773600
			},
			"text": " can select the right project."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:12:53,600",
				"to": "00:13:01,400"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 773600,
				"to": 781400
			},
			"text": " Bokey decides that the best one to support is the two-factor authentication project for"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:01,400",
				"to": "00:13:02,840"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 781400,
				"to": 782840
			},
			"text": " my Ether wallet."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:02,840",
				"to": "00:13:06,600"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 782840,
				"to": 786600
			},
			"text": " So he pre-commits the Ether."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:06,600",
				"to": "00:13:16,160"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 786600,
				"to": 796160
			},
			"text": " At this point, GAB has three days or any time pre-configured to veto if he does not agree"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:16,160",
				"to": "00:13:18,160"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 796160,
				"to": 798160
			},
			"text": " with Bokey's choice."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:18,160",
				"to": "00:13:25,880"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 798160,
				"to": 805880
			},
			"text": " But if he does nothing, my Ether wallet project is a great supporter."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:25,880",
				"to": "00:13:33,080"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 805880,
				"to": 813080
			},
			"text": " This can be a normal account or can have a smart contract plugin attached where a reviewer,"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:33,080",
				"to": "00:13:42,000"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 813080,
				"to": 822000
			},
			"text": " let's call this reviewer, if GRIF decides that the work is done, the Ether go to Taylor"
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:42,000",
				"to": "00:13:47,000"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 822000,
				"to": 827000
			},
			"text": " for successfully implementing two-factor authentication."
		},
		{
			"timestamps": {
				"from": "00:13:47,000",
				"to": "00:13:53,760"
			},
			"offsets": {
				"from": 827000,
				"to": 833760
			},
			"text": " But if the project does not meet the conditions in the given amount of time, he can cancel"
		},
